    <section id="structure">
      <h2>Using Semantic Tags</h2>
      <p>HTML5 provides meaningful elements like <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;main&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;section&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;article&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code> to organize content in a logical way.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="accessibility">
      <h2>Accessibility Best Practices</h2>
      <p>Use clear heading hierarchies, add <code>alt</code> attributes for images, and landmarks like <code>&lt;main&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> to guide screen readers.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="seo">
      <h2>SEO-Friendly Strategies</h2>
      <p>Write descriptive titles, use keywords thoughtfully, and organize content so it's readable by both users and search engine crawlers.</p>
    </section>
